16/03/2004
WASHINGTON, United States -- The House of Representatives has submitted a resolution recommending that the Adriatic Charter countries -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- accede to NATO by 2007. According to the resolution, the three countries have demonstrated their devotion to the principles and values of the Pact. Debate is expected to begin Wednesday (17 March). (MIA, Makfax - 15/03/04)
